Hardware-Powered Luau Proxies
High-speed middleware for external API communication and Admin logging.
This module acts as a secure bridge between your Roblox game servers and external web services. It is optimized to handle high-frequency requests (like chat logs or rank updates) without triggering 429 rate limits or bottlenecking your server’s performance.

# ---WHAT-TO-EXPECT---
1. These are currently in beta-mode.
2. V3 Is lately arriving with a bunch of new of these features.
3. Final, proxy modules are included to insert with the OrbitBar Graphic-User-Interface Script.

Module.la Proxies example:

local Proxy = require(game.ServerStorage.ProxyHandler)

-- Sending a standard log to your external registry
Proxy.Post({
    Url = "https://your-github-proxy.com/api/logs",
    Headers = { ["Authorization"] = "Bearer DI_TEAM_KEY" },
    Body = {
        User = "YourUsernameHere",
        Action = "RankUpdate",
        NewRank = "Owner",
        XP = 650000
    }
})

Another example to help:

local RegistryProxy = require(game.ServerStorage.RegistryProxy)

-- Fetch the latest rank data from GitHub
local Success, Data = RegistryProxy.FetchRegistry("MainBranch")

if Success then
    print(" Admin Request Requirement: " .. Data.Ranks.Mod)
end

